
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-wing-pcp-third-party-authz-03.txt'>
    <title>"PCP Extension for Third Party Authorization", Dan Wing, Tirumaleswar Reddy, Prashanth Patil, Reinaldo Penno</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-wing-pcp-third-party-authz-03.txt</link>
    <description>It is often desirable for an application server to permit a flow across a firewall, as happens today when a firewall includes an Application Layer Gateway (ALG) function.  However, an ALG has several weaknesses.  This document describes a cryptographic technique for an application server to permit a flow across a firewall.  This technique uses OAuth and a new PCP option.</description>
    <dc:date>2014-04-02T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
